// Construct the absolute path to the file using __dirname
const filePath = path.join(__dirname, fileName);

// Now you can use the `filePath` in your code to reference the file
```

In this example, `__dirname` represents the path to the directory where your code file is located. By using `path.join()`, you can concatenate the `__dirname` with the file name to get the absolute path to the file. You can then use the `filePath` variable to reference the file in your code.

